The paper deals with motion planning for robotic arms, which is a core topic in robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method involves building a discrete approximation of a navigation function, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the method on tasks involving clutter, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The method involves informed sampling-based planning, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the method involves exploring alternative paths over time, which is a common technique in control systems (cs.SY).
